53    /**
54    * Represents JavaScript value types.<p>
55    *
56    * Types are split into two separate families: value types and object types.
57    *
58    * A special {@link UnknownType} exists to represent a wildcard type on which
59    * no information can be gathered. In particular, it can assign to everyone,
60    * is a subtype of everyone (and everyone is a subtype of it).<p>
61    *
62    * If you remove the {@link UnknownType}, the set of types in the type system
63    * forms a lattice with the {@link #isSubtype} relation defining the partial
64    * order of types. All types are united at the top of the lattice by the
65    * {@link AllType} and at the bottom by the {@link NoType}.<p>
66    *
67    */

1306    /**
1307    * Checks whether {@code this} is a subtype of {@code that}.<p>
1308    *
1309    * Subtyping rules:
1310    * <ul>
1311    * <li>(unknown) &mdash; every type is a subtype of the Unknown type.</li>
1312    * <li>(no) &mdash; the No type is a subtype of every type.</li>
1313    * <li>(no-object) &mdash; the NoObject type is a subtype of every object
1314    * type (i.e. subtypes of the Object type).</li>
1315    * <li>(ref) &mdash; a type is a subtype of itself.</li>
1316    * <li>(union-l) &mdash; A union type is a subtype of a type U if all the
1317    * union type's constituents are a subtype of U. Formally<br>
1318    * {@code (T<sub>1</sub>, &hellip;, T<sub>n</sub>) &lt;: U} if and only
1319    * {@code T<sub>k</sub> &lt;: U} for all {@code k &isin; 1..n}.</li>
1320    * <li>(union-r) &mdash; A type U is a subtype of a union type if it is a
1321    * subtype of one of the union type's constituents. Formally<br>
1322    * {@code U &lt;: (T<sub>1</sub>, &hellip;, T<sub>n</sub>)} if and only
1323    * if {@code U &lt;: T<sub>k</sub>} for some index {@code k}.</li>
1324    * <li>(objects) &mdash; an Object {@code O<sub>1</sub>} is a subtype
1325    * of an object {@code O<sub>2</sub>} if it has more properties
1326    * than {@code O<sub>2</sub>} and all common properties are
1327    * pairwise subtypes.</li>
1328    * </ul>
1329    *
1330    * @return {@code this &lt;: that}
1331    */
